  <h1>
   webgl_enabled
  </h1>
  This
  <b>
   read-only
  </b>
  variable will return whether WebGL is enabled (
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  ) or not (
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  ) for your game. It will only work for those games running through a browser (ie: HTML5), and for all other platforms it will return true.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">webgl_enabled
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if webgl_enabled
{
    global.quality = 1;
}
else global.quality = 0;
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the WebGL flag and then sets the global variable "quality" accordingly.
 </body>
</html>